# Agent Delegation (Cursor)

Use `mcp_task` with `subagent_type` to delegate focused subtasks to specialized agents.

## OBLIGATORIO antes de cualquier tarea (incl. planes)

Si el agente va a ejecutar un **plan** o cualquier tarea de edición: verificar rama con `git branch --show-current`. Si está en `main` o `develop`, crear rama feature primero (ver regla `git-workflow`). NUNCA editar en develop.

## OBLIGATORIO al finalizar un plan o tarea

1. **Commitear los cambios.** NUNCA terminar con cambios sin commitear. Ejecutar `git status`, `git add` de archivos relevantes, `git commit -m "tipo: descripción"`.
2. **NO hacer `git checkout develop`** sin merge previo. Quedarse en la rama feature con los commits aplicados. Si el usuario quiere merge, usar `/finish`.
3. **Persistir el trabajo:** los agentes Cursor deben guardar el resultado de su trabajo. No revertir ni descartar cambios.

## When to delegate

| Scenario | subagent_type | Use when |
|----------|---------------|----------|
| Code review | `code-reviewer` | User asks for code review, quality check, or validation before commit |
| Write/fix tests | `test-writer` | User needs comprehensive tests, coverage improvement, or failing test fixes |
| Git operations | `git-ops` | User needs branching, conventional commits, or merge to develop |
| Implement UI/UX design | `ui-designer` | User needs to implement or correct design in components, templates, or tokens |
| Create/modify SVG | `svg-designer` | User needs SVG icons, illustrations, or decorative elements |
| Design audit | `design-verifier` | User asks to verify design UI/UX only. Read-only, no code changes |

## Usage

- **code-reviewer**: Read-only review. Does not modify code. Runs lint + tests and reports issues.
- **test-writer**: Creates or fixes tests. Uses Vitest + RTL patterns. Can read, write, edit, run bash.
- **git-ops**: Manages git only. Never modifies source. Handles branch creation, commits, merges.
- **ui-designer**: Implements design system. Follows ui-design skill. Can read, write, edit.
- **svg-designer**: Implements SVG graphics. Follows svg-design skill. Can read, write, edit.
- **design-verifier**: Read-only design audit. Applies design-audit checklist. Reports palette, contrast, responsive. Does not run lint/tests/build.

## Skills that may delegate

- `/component` and `/template`: delegate test creation to test-writer when tests are complex
- `/test`: delegate to test-writer for comprehensive test coverage
- `/validate`: can delegate to code-reviewer for full review + validation
- `/task` and `/finish`: git-ops handles branching and merges; main agent can also execute directly per skill steps
- ui-design skill: delegate to ui-designer for design implementation
- svg-design skill: delegate to svg-designer for SVG work
- Design verification: delegate to design-verifier for design audit
